{
  "stem": "13469.8",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The interesting thing about the MBE, apart from getting it of course, and the subsequent visit to Buckingham Palace, the interesting thing about the MBE was that local reporters came around to interview me from the and the And they said, how old are you and how long have you lived here and where did you live before, where were you born?",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And within five questions, every reporter had found out that I'd been to Belsen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they forgot about the MBE and they all wanted to know about Belsen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was this headline, 'MBE for Belsen Survivor' and all these kinds of things in the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one of the photographers that came along, he was a war buff in touch with the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he said-- this was 1990, January-- and he said, did you know that there is a big event in Belsen this year, in April, 1990, because it's 45 years after the liberation of Belsen?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's also Yom HaShoah, Day of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it's also the opening of a new documentation center in Belsen in April, 1990.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I said, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't know anything about that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he got me all the information and he got me really interested.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he said, would you like to go?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we thought about it here, my family, which I better mention as well in a minute.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We thought about it and eventually Ritchie, my brother, and my daughter, Judith, who was 18, 19 at that time and very much interested in Judaism and the Holocaust, the three of us together with a press photographer and an editor from the we went back to Belsen in 1990 for the commemoration ceremony, spent the weekend there.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We met lots of other survivors.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
